data.name: lblDescStep2Download.Text
data.value: You chose that you are downloading a game or some kind of update. The right time to turn of your computer would be when the download is finished. To determine the right time, you need to enter your download speed and the size of the download.

data.name: lblDescStep2AFK.Text
data.value: You chose that you are AFKing in some game. In that case it depends on why you AFK. If you are farming items for example, you should find out how many items you approximately get per minute to determine the right time to shut down your PC. In case you are AFKing for something that hasn't a pretty much linear drop rate (e.g. different drop chances), you can pretty much just guess on how long it will take.

data.name: lblDescStep3.Text
data.value:
The Time Helper Wizard has been completed!
Please note that the time is only an approximate calculation and may be wrong. If you are copying important files for example, you should watch out when using a scheduled shut down. In any case, the developer is not liable for any damage that may be caused. Also, none of the information you have entered will be sent to any server.
